
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    `gnome-calculator` yek narm afzar hesabdari graphical ast ke dar mohite GNOME baraye mohasebat riazi estefade mishavad. Mitavanad amaliat haye sade va pishrafte riazi ra anjam dahad. 🧮

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--version` --> ℹ️ Namayesh version-e narm afzar.
    🔹 `--help`    --> ❓ Namayesh rahnama (help) darbare dastoor va gozine-ha.
    🔹 Nadashtane gozine --> 🚀 Ba ejraye sade, narm afzar baaz mishavad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gnome-calculator

    🔹 Baaz kardane narm afzar hesabdari GNOME ba interface graphical.

    $ gnome-calculator --version

    🔹 Namayesh version-e narm afzar hesabdari.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gnome-calculator &

    🔹 Narm afzar hesabdari ra dar background ejra mikonad va terminal ra azad mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    `gnome-calculator` is a graphical calculator application used in the GNOME environment for mathematical calculations. It can perform simple and advanced mathematical operations. 🧮

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--version` --> ℹ️ Display the software version.
    🔹 `--help`    --> ❓ Display help information about the command and options.
    🔹 No options  --> 🚀 Running it without options opens the calculator application.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gnome-calculator

    🔹 Opens the GNOME calculator application with the graphical interface.

    $ gnome-calculator --version

    🔹 Displays the version of the calculator application.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gnome-calculator &

    🔹 Runs the calculator application in the background, freeing up the terminal.

